videos.voice_over: Here's the secret no one tells you when you're feeling lost at 25. You're not behind, you're just early. Most of us are supposed to have our career, our purpose, and our relationships figured out by now. But that timeline is made up. Here's how to stay calm and turn it around. First, pick a 12-month obsession, not a 10-year plan. Choose one skill that could raise your earning potential and go all in for one year before judging yourself. Second, treat your strategy. Sleep, train, and eat in a way that gives you energy. You can't build a better life exhausted. Third, upgrade the five people you spend the most time with. If they don't inspire you or push you, reduce their influence and find people who do. And fourth, play the volume game. More reps, create more opportunities. Fly more, reach out more, publish more. Action kills anxiety. Nobody actually has it all figured out at 25. They just keep moving. Stay patient, stay consistent. Your life can look completely different in 12 months if you start today.

videos.voice_over: I'm getting so many messages from my younger audience lately asking me for my advice as to what they should do and which career path to take after finishing high school. I honestly remember that feeling so well. I used to envy the people who always knew exactly what they wanted ‚Äî the type that say "I wanted to be a doctor since I was six" or "I'm definitely gonna be a lawyer." I never had that. I was always curious about different things: languages, culture, history, politics, economics. I felt like the traditional school system wasn't really built for someone like me. What I learned is that not having one clear direction does not mean you're lost ‚Äî it means you're open, and that's incredibly powerful. We live in a time with many possibilities, and that freedom can feel overwhelming. videos.voice_over: this past Friday I saw this article in New York magazine which is the job search has become a humiliation ritual and I'm going to say first up top I get that you know like I hear that from people that I talk with and I wanna talk about this article where I'm both going to pull some quotes and make some commentary on it and then I'm going to give a little bit of advice at the end please know that this is coming from a place of hoping to help people who are on the job search I am somebody who has worked in HR in New York City for many years and I'm a little bit of a nerd when it comes to career content and I read a lot about the these things and professional development so just stick with me for the journey but the first piece that I wanna kick off with is kind of this funny quote that was actually used on their Instagram page where one of the people that they interviewed said I will certainly not get a job I don't apply to David notes Riley I will almost certainly not get a job I do apply to and that almost is why I keep applying it's like going to services for a religion I don't believe in it's a ritual I thought that that was funny but also like sadly true and I wanted to start with that that I wanna highlight is this kind of quote that really stuck out at me and stopped me a bit of my tracks job insecurity and unemployment can eat self esteem produce the drowning buzz of crippling anxiety shorten the range of a person's hope and belief in the system in their future in themselves it can produce zero sum suspicious thinking slowly and insidiously making people see other people as their competition and wondering if their identities are a small part of the reasons they are getting passed over the mental health impact of long term unemployment is well observed in research people on the job search for a long time struggle with anxiety depression feelings of failure and both real and perceived social stigma the dishwasher is finished so this sticks out to me because I personally was unemployed in 2020 in the time in which things were shutting down and covid and for lows and a lot of mass layoffs but what was different in that time is that it almost felt like there wasn't a social stigma because if you lost your job cuz of covid it was like okay well that makes sense because everybody's losing their job I personally can't imagine losing my job now which is why I empathize so much with job seekers and I try to on my page help people out and give some ideas or tricks of the trade that I have found over the last couple years the other thing that I want to highlight and then this will segway us into the advice portion of this video if you choose to take it if you want to it's up to you we've long been sold the idea of work as identity purpose and social mobility so what happens if the machine breaks down when people are doing everything right networking optimising trawling LinkedIn and still hearing nothing back what does it feel like to search for employment now to swim against the current in the sea of American insecurity well for starters shout out to whoever wrote this article because it is very well written and it sorry it is written by I'm gonna get it right uh Sarah think and Matthews so shout out to you but here we are going to move into the advice portion of this number one they mentioned this in the article don't easy apply easy apply is not the way to go always go to a company's website don't just easy apply on LinkedIn go to their website and apply directly there number two is related be intentional I know that it feels really easy to just press apply apply apply and play the numbers game but I don't think that job searching is always a numbers game I think that you need to be really thoughtful and intentional and write the cover letter tailor the resume reach out to the right people that's what you have to do as annoying as it may sometimes feel and then the third piece is the advice that I know you all have heard many times but it is true that your network is everything connections that you have and they don't have to be fancy people they don't have to have big titles they don't have to be overly successful they can just simply be people that you have met who have showed you kindness and can help you out and kind of nudge you in the right direction you would be surprised at the little pockets of your world that you would be able to find someone who can help you out in your next chapter of your career

videos.voice_over: job market looking like right now in November 2025. Let's talk about it. In this video, I'm going to break down the current job market across three different metrics and then give it a score out of 10. I'll also share my thoughts on where I think the market's heading. My name's Omar and I talk economics, jobs, and everything near NYC. So if you're into some spicy hot takes, then today's case a monthly job market update, smash up that like and hit follow. Okay, so the first metric we're going to take a look at today's unemployment rate. And as you can see based on this graph, this thing's been stuck at 4.3% for the past few months. And that's really because our government's shut down, they're not working, they're not updating this data. So not much to see here. Let's move on to the next metric. The second metric we usually take a look at is job openings. And as you can see based on this graph, we've been stuck at 7.2 million K for the past few months. Again, this is because of the government shut down, this data is outdated. Not a whole lot to see here. Let's move on to the last metric. The third metric we're going to take a look at today's the Fed Funds interest rate. And there's finally been some movement here. As you can see based on this graph, we've gone down from 4.25% to 4% and that's a great step in the right direction. The reason why this metric is important is because when the Fed Funds interest rate is high, companies have less money to invest in new jobs, new projects, new growth opportunities. All those good things that keep moving the economy forward. And the more the Fed cuts these interest rates, the more jobs will hit the market. We obviously saw two rate cuts very recently. But a lot of people believe there's another one coming in December. So when that finally happens, and hopefully the government has opened back up by then, we should see much better unemployment rates and much better job openings as well. So with these three metrics factored in, I'm going to give the November job market a total score of 4.5 out of 10. If you guys watched my video from last month, you'll know that this is half a point higher than what I gave the October job market. And the reason for this comes down to the rate cuts that we finally saw come through. Looking ahead, I do see the job market continuing to improve, but it's going to be a slow process getting there, and it's going to come on the back of these rate cuts. We obviously saw two rate cuts very recently, but a lot of people believe there's another one coming in December. So when that finally happens, and hopefully the government has opened back up by then, we should see much better unemployment rates and much better job openings as well.

videos.title: The Three Musketeers is a Rare card that is unlocked from the Royal Arena (Arena 7). It spawns three Musketeers in a triangle formation. A Three Musketeers card costs 9 Elixir to deploy. The Three Musketeers have massive damage per second and can be split into both lanes, which can make them extremely threatening on offense or defense. However, playing this card incurs a huge risk due to its high cost potentially resulting in a large Elixir profit for the opponent. Additionally, the player will have very little Elixir to deploy other cards immediately afterwards. When deploying the Three Musketeers, the player should place them close to or in the back of the Arena, as they are easily countered alone. Splitting them is recommended since the opponent cannot gain as much value with spells, usually allowing one Musketeer to walk into the other lane unscathed. Splitting them can also discourage the opponent from attacking either lane, due to their defensive presence. A quickly-placed Tornado can deny this split attempt if the Musketeers are placed on the tiles closest to the center of the Arena, but it will often activate the King's Tower due to its large radius. When splitting the Three Musketeers, the player should generally support the weaker lane more than the stronger lane. This can make the pushes in both lanes nearly equally as powerful, making it difficult for the opponent to decide which lane to spend more Elixir in. videos.voice_over: I don't care if I have to restart a million times. I won't settle for a life I don't want. Peace hits different when you've earned it the hard way. I've seen what settling looks like. It's quiet misery that people dress up as stability. It's pretending you're fine because you're scared to start over. But starting over isn't failure. It's self-respect. Sometimes you gotta burn a version of your life that looked good on paper, but didn't feel good in your soul. Starting hurts. You lose people, you lose time, you lose comfort. But every time you rebuild, you do it with more wisdom, more boundaries, and less fear. People will call it inconsistency. It's not. It's refusing to live half a life. It's knowing you deserve a life that feels like you. Not one that just looks impressive from the outside. So yeah, I'll restart a million times if I have to. I don't care how long it takes, how messy it gets, or who doesn't understand. I'm not settling for a life that doesn't feel like mine, because peace costs less than pretending.

videos.title: You know when people say ‚Äúyou have to feel it to heal it‚Äù or to ‚Äúprocess trauma‚Äù? THIS is what they‚Äôre talking about. When something painful happened in your past, your body tried to protect you. It geared up to do something ‚Äî run, fight, yell, push, speak ‚Äî but you couldn‚Äôt. You weren‚Äôt ‚Äúfrozen‚Äù as in shut down‚Ä¶ you were stopped. Your healthy survival response got interrupted mid-way, and that leftover energy stayed stuck in your muscles, breath, and nervous system. Healing doesn‚Äôt mean re-living the trauma. It means letting your body finish the ‚Äúsurvival impulse‚Äù it couldn‚Äôt finish back then. It‚Äôs the biological version of finally exhaling after holding your breath for years. Here‚Äôs how to do it safely: 1. Pick a small memory that still bothers you. 2. Hold it lightly for a moment ‚Äî just enough to feel a sensation in your body. 3. Ask: ‚ÄúWhat did my body want to do back then?‚Äù (Run? Push? Say ‚ÄúStop‚Äù? Move away?) 4. Do a tiny, symbolic version of that movement now: press your hands against a wall, stomp, shake it out, or say ‚ÄúNo.‚Äù 5. Breathe slowly and tell yourself: ‚ÄúThat was then. This is now. I‚Äôm safe.‚Äù This is how your nervous system finally completes the loop and releases the energy that‚Äôs been trapped for years. That‚Äôs what healing actually means ‚Äî not thinking about it, but letting your body finish the story.  #traumahealing #feelittohealit #somatichealing #nervoussystemhealing #trauma

videos.title: The Three Musketeers is a Rare card that is unlocked from the Royal Arena (Arena 7). It spawns three Musketeers in a triangle formation. A Three Musketeers card costs 9 Elixir to deploy. The Three Musketeers have massive damage per second and can be split into both lanes, which can make them extremely threatening on offense or defense. However, playing this card incurs a huge risk due to its high cost potentially resulting in a large Elixir profit for the opponent. Additionally, the player will have very little Elixir to deploy other cards immediately afterwards. When deploying the Three Musketeers, the player should place them close to or in the back of the Arena, as they are easily countered alone. Splitting them is recommended since the opponent cannot gain as much value with spells, usually allowing one Musketeer to walk into the other lane unscathed. Splitting them can also discourage the opponent from attacking either lane, due to their defensive presence. A quickly-placed Tornado can deny this split attempt if the Musketeers are placed on the tiles closest to the center of the Arena, but it will often activate the King's Tower due to its large radius. When splitting the Three Musketeers, the player should generally support the weaker lane more than the stronger lane. This can make the pushes in both lanes nearly equally as powerful, making it difficult for the opponent to decide which lane to spend more Elixir in. Spells such as the FireballRoyal Delivery and ZapGiant SnowballThe Log combo, Poison, Rocket, and Lightning will all counter the trio for a positive Elixir trade anywhere in the Arena. Excluding Lightning, all these spells deal area damage, allowing the defender to reap even more value. However, when using spell counters, one should pay extra attention if any of them deal knockback, since some spell combos may miss due to inaccurate timing. Lightning can also be blocked by higher hitpoint units surrounding the Three Musketeers. #fyp #clashroyale #jynxzi #riley #nonutnovember @7Ô∏è‚É£9Ô∏è‚É£ @paxton @ ô·¥ò @Richard @Chopper @anger @JorL6161
